.TH "__devm_alloc_percpu" 9 "__devm_alloc_percpu" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
__devm_alloc_percpu \- Resource-managed alloc_percpu
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void __percpu *" __devm_alloc_percpu
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "size_t size "  ","
.BI "size_t align "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
Device to allocate per-cpu memory for
.IP "size" 12
Size of per-cpu memory to allocate
.IP "align" 12
Alignment of per-cpu memory to allocate
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Managed alloc_percpu. Per-cpu memory allocated with this function is
automatically freed on driver detach.
.SH "RETURN"
Pointer to allocated memory on success, NULL on failure.
